elements userinput userinput Element
userinput &userinput.purpose;
&userinput.synopsis.gen; Description
The UserInput element identifies words or phrases that the user is expected to provide as input to a computer program.
Note that UserInput is not a verbatim environment, but an inline.
Processing expectations
&format.inline; &pexp.moreinfo; Often presented in a fixed width font.
&FutureChanges;
&fu.interfacedefinition;
&userinput.parents.gen; &userinput.children.gen;
Attributes
moreinfo
If MoreInfo is set to RefEntry, it implies that a RefEntry exists which further describes the UserInput.
See Also &userinput.seealso.gen;
